 7. As CEO, I manage Shift4’s executives and oversee all
 aspects of Shift4’s global business ventures. As a general practice, I
 do not weigh in on technical or operational matters.
 8. In July 2018, I was generally aware that that First Data
 had recently acquired CardConnect, and that the CardConnect gateway
 would be “sunsetted” in favor of the payment gateway previously
 owned by First Data.
 9. Based on the CardConnect acquisition, I anticipated that
 CardConnect would no longer exist in short order.
10. Further, as a competitor of Shift4, I did not believe it was
 prudent for Shift4 to expend resources helping CardConnect transfer
 its payment gateway to First Data.
12. As to the email and text communications in July and August
2018 (attached as Ex. A), I believed at the time, and still believe
today, that my concerns about maintaining reselling/partner
relationships with 1,800+ “CardConnect ISOs” were valid.
13. I did not ask, direct, instruct, or otherwise authorize
anyone at Shift4 to block CardConnect, or take any action whatsoever
regarding CardConnect.
14. Although I received an email from Jared Isaacman suggesting he had the technical capability to “block” CardConnect from the Shift4 gateway, I did not authorize, encourage, or otherwise respond to Mr. Isaacman’s suggestion.
15.I was travelling at the time, and had only my iPhone,
which made responding to emails more difficult than otherwise.
16.I did not follow up with Jared Isaacman on his suggestion that
he could block CardConnect.
